StellarOSCVocabulary.FilterDirectives - Class in com.stellarcommand
The parameters we will use to define our filters
The actual parameter filtered will be before with its value as the OSC argument
eg Hpmagr/less 6 will filter Hpmagr for values less than 6
All filters are ANDed together
eg filter/Hpmagr/less 6 followed by filter/Hpmagr/greater 1 will filter Hpmagr between 6 and 1
StellarOSCVocabulary.ReceiveMessages - Class in com.stellarcommand
ReceiveMessages are sent from OSC client to StellarCommand Direct where our message will be filtered
StellarOSCVocabulary.SendMessages - Class in com.stellarcommand
SendMessages are the messages sent from StellarCommand to the OSC client

vizier - package vizier
 
vizierData - Variable in class StellarStructures.StellarDataRow
 
VizierQuery - Class in vizier
Class for querying VizieR catalogue of astronomical catalogues Sample query Default catalogue used is I/311/hip2 - Hipparcos, the New Reduction (van Leeuwen, 2007) Default outputs are as follows
RArad (deg) (F12.8) Right Ascension in ICRS, Ep=1991.25 [ucd=pos.eq.ra;meta.main]
DErad (deg) (F12.8) Declination in ICRS, Ep=1991.25 [ucd=pos.eq.dec;meta.main]
pmRA (mas/yr) (F8.2) Proper motion in Right Ascension [ucd=pos.pm;pos.eq.ra]
pmDE (mas/yr) (F8.2) Proper motion in Declination [ucd=pos.pm;pos.eq.dec]
Hpmag (mag) (F7.4) Hipparcos magnitude [ucd=phot.mag;em.opt.V]
B-V (mag) (F6.3) Colour index [ucd=phot.color;em.opt.B;em.opt.V]

See http://vizier.u-strasbg.fr/vizier/doc/vizquery.htx for details about query
VizierQuery() - Constructor for class vizier.VizierQuery
